Entering Mogadishu | World's Most Dangerous City
Spending a day in the most Dangerous Hood in Kenya\"

In South Kivu in Congo, the city of Shabunda is one of the most isolated in the country. Its access is so difficult that life is more expensive there than in any European city. These convicts of the road sometimes transport up to 250 kilos of goods for several days, without worrying about the dangers.
